"script": "What if I told you one U.S. President became a billionaire before entering politics? Donald Trump wasn't a career politician. He built his public image through real estate, hotels, golf courses, and television. In 2015, he announced his presidential campaign, and just one year later, he defeated experienced politicians to become the 45th President of the United States. After leaving office, he made history again by winning the 2024 election, becoming only the second U.S. President ever to serve two non-consecutive terms. Whether people support him or not, his political comeback is one of the most unusual in American history.",
